Correct Ans: All of the above. In R, `$`, `[` and `[[` are used for indexing. The most important difference between `[`, `[[` and `$` is that the `[` can select more than one elements while the other two select a single element. #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:03052022220007]

The main difference between `$` and `[[` is that `$` does not allow computed indices whereas `[[` does. `z[['a']]` is equivalent to `z$a`. `[[` can be applied recursively to lists as shown in option 3, `z[[c('a', 'c')]]` is #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:03052022220007]
equivalent to `z[['a']][['c']]`. #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:03052022220007]
